60|$|In {{the evening}} {{he went to}} Dryholm and dined with Bernard at a small table in the spacious room. Afterwards they sat by the fire talking quietly. Flickering {{reflections}} played about the carved marble and bright steel; electric lights, half-hidden by the cornice, threw down a soft light, and Bernard looked old and worn as <b>he</b> <b>leaned</b> <b>back</b> languidly <b>in</b> his big chair.|$|R
